api_list.name: /timePeriod
api_list.description: The 'timePeriod' endpoint in the MentalHealthCareFile API provides a list of different time periods associated with mental health care files. These time periods represent specific durations or intervals that are relevant to the mental health care records. This endpoint returns an array of strings, which are essentially text values that describe these time periods. You can think of these strings as labels or categories that help organize the mental health care files based on their time-related attributes. For example, the endpoint might return time periods such as '1 month,' '6 months,' or '1 year' to indicate the length of time for which a particular mental health care file has been active or updated. These values serve as options for users to choose from when filtering or searching for specific time periods within the mental health care files.By utilizing the 'timePeriod' endpoint, users can easily gather information about the various time spans associated with mental health care records, making it convenient to analyze and categorize data based on different timeframes.

With this endpoint, stakeholders can gain a better understanding of the data and make informed decisions to improve mental health care practices.

It allows for a better understanding of the specific challenges individuals face in accessing appropriate care and can help inform strategies aimed at improving mental health support for those in need.

api_list.name: /highci
api_list.description: The endpoint 'highci' in the 'MentalHealthCareFile' API provides a list of possible values for the 'highci' field. This field represents the confidence interval associated with a high-level indicator in mental health care. Imagine you are measuring different aspects of mental health care, such as the effectiveness of treatments or the satisfaction of patients. The 'highci' field gives you an idea of the range within which the estimated values for these indicators can vary.For example, let's say you receive a 'highci' value of 27.6. This means that the estimated value for the indicator has a high level of confidence and can vary within a range of plus or minus 27.6 units. Similarly, a 'highci' value of 6.6 suggests a narrower range of variation.By accessing this endpoint, you can obtain an array of strings that represent various possible 'highci' values. These values enable you to understand the level of uncertainty associated with the mental health care indicators and make more informed decisions based on the confidence intervals.

api_list.name: /confidenceInterval
api_list.description: The 'confidenceInterval' endpoint in the MentalHealthCareFile API provides a range of values that indicate the level of certainty or precision associated with certain data. It returns an array of strings that represent different possible confidence intervals. A confidence interval is often used in statistical analysis to estimate the range within which the true value of a particular measurement or statistic is likely to fall. For example, if a confidence interval is 95%, it means that there is a 95% probability that the true value lies within the specified range.In the MentalHealthCareFile API, the 'confidenceInterval' endpoint presents various confidence intervals that can be associated with mental health care data. Each string in the array represents a different range of values, indicating the level of confidence or uncertainty in the corresponding data.Using these confidence intervals, users can assess the reliability and accuracy of the mental health care information provided by the API. The endpoint helps users understand the range within which the actual values may exist, allowing for informed decision-making and analysis in the field of mental health care.
